                            ATime Documentation
                               Bill Koester

ATime is a PC C program that uses the Amiga Service TimeServ to set the
PC's system date and time from the Amigas clock.

Usage:
  ATime       ;Set date and time only if TimeServ is already running.
  ATime /w    ;Wait for the TimeServ service to become available.

The source code for this command is provided in the docs/developer directory.

See Also:
  TimeServ.DOC, ASetTime.DOC
